[thinking] **Investigating JaCoCo Execution**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering if executing via MethodHandle is using an uninstrumented class. It seems like tests might run against the original dependency jar while the report uses the instrumented one. In Gradle, the javaTest with the JaCoCo agent tends to collect coverage for the original classes, and it did for SSLConfig. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] Maybe JaCoCo excludes the class$ method due to missing line info. It could also be that dynamic access coverage requires line coverage, but I'm not entirely sure. I think I should inspect the JaCoCo report for more insights.
[thinking] 
